sql:
SELECT products.product_name, products.product_type, (prices.discounted_price - prices.mrp) AS price_difference
FROM products
JOIN prices ON products.product_id = prices.product_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Spirits' refers to a category of alcoholic beverages; 
- A discounted price under 100 implies a specific price range; 
- Being 'available in stock' means the quantity_in_stock is greater than 0; 
- 'Sold after 2023' refers to any sale_date after '2023-01-01'; 
- 'Profit margin' is calculated based on the sale amount, discounted price, and product ID, using the formula ((s.sale_amount - pr.discounted_price) * 1.0 / (p.product_id * p.product_id)).
